[{"location":"95-reference/#reference","page":"Reference","title":"Reference","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"95-reference/#Contents","page":"Reference","title":"Contents","text":"Pages = [\"95-reference.md\"]","category":"section"},{"location":"95-reference/#Index","page":"Reference","title":"Index","text":"Pages = [\"95-reference.md\"]","category":"section"},{"location":"95-reference/#CallableModules.@module_main-Tuple{Any}","page":"Reference","title":"CallableModules.@module_main","text":"@module_main funcdef\n\nMake the enclosing module callable by forwarding MyModule(args...; kwargs...) to the annotated function.\n\nExamples\n\nmodule MyApp\n    using CallableModules\n    @module_main function main(args...; kwargs...)\n        println(\"args=$args, kwargs=$kwargs\")\n    end\nend\n\nMyApp(1, 2; verbose=true)\n# args=(1, 2), kwargs=Base.Pairs(:verbose => true)\n\nBoth long-form (function f(...) ... end) and short-form (f(x) = ...) definitions are supported.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"macro"},{"location":"#CallableModules","page":"CallableModules","title":"CallableModules","text":"Documentation for CallableModules.","category":"section"}]
